[Up-to-date] Reference: https://docs.kernel.org/process/submitting-patches.html

git checkout -b proc_jiffies_patch
git branch

cp proc_jiffies.c fs/proc
vim Kconfig
vim Makefile

git add .
git commit
	Expose jiffies variable via /proc/jiffies

	This patch adds support for exposing jiffies variable via
	/proc/jiffies - which can be useful sometimes in user-space
	instrumentation and diagnostics.

mkdir /root/patches master
git format-patch -o /root/patches [anylocation]
	generated: /root/patches/001-Expose-jiffies-variable-via-proc-jiffies.patch

//Not suggest to set the parameter -> it is annoying & blacklist you!
git send-email --to=xxx master [the maintainer of the subsystem of the kernel]
	how to find them? scripts/get_maintainer.pl -f fs/proc/Kconfig
	enter this command --> will generate the email

git help send-email [list all the options in my patch email]

git checkout -b test_patch
git branch
git status [verify the branch]

git apply /root/patches/001-Expose-jiffies-variable-via-proc-jiffies.patch
git status

ls Document/process [if you want to do the patches]
	- understanding & working with the community
	- **coding-style.rst [Linus expected coding style]
